        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-02-25 19:49:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThis is a good starting point, but much more in this direction to be done (ignoring build/autogen.sh, which is already being updated in a separate patch):\n\nbuild/doxygen-footer.html:<small><a href=\"http://www.sun.com/contact\">Contact</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.sun.com/aboutsun/index.html\">About Sun</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.sun.com/aboutsun/media/index.html\">\nbuild/doxygen-header.html:<img src=\"http://wiki.lustre.org/apidoc/header.jpg\">\nbuild/lbuild:            local location=\"http://downloads.lustre.org/public/kernels/$target/old\"\nldiskfs/autoMakefile.am:                echo -e \"I have no idea how to create a META file in $(distdir).\\nPlease file a bug at http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\"; \\\nlustre/BUGS:To report bugs, please visit http://bugzilla.lustre.org/lustre/BUILDING:kernel and utilities from http://downloads.lustre.org/\nlustre/BUILDING:  http://www.lustre.org/\n\nlustre/doc/lctl.8:Please report all bugs to Sun Microsystems, Inc. http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/lctl.8:http://www.sun.com/software/products/lustre/index.xml\nlustre/doc/lfs.1:Report bugs using http://bugzilla.lustre.org.\nlustre/doc/lfs.1:The lfs command is part of the Lustre filesystem.  Contact http://www.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/lfs_migrate.1:Please report all bugs to http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/lustre.7:is under active development from Sun Microsystems (http://www.lustre.org).\nlustre/doc/lustre.7:Please report all bugs to Sun Microsystems via http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/lustre.7:http://downloads.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/lustre_rsync.8:http://www.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/mkfs.lustre.8:Please report all bugs to Sun Microsystems via http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/mkfs.lustre.8:http://downloads.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/mount.lustre.8:Please report all bugs to Sun Microsystems using http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\nlustre/doc/mount.lustre.8:http://downloads.lustre.org\nl\nlustre/lvfs/fsfilt_ext3.c: \"http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\\n\");\nlustre/obdfilter/filter.c: \"http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\\n\",\nlustre/obdfilter/filter.c: \"http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\\n\",\nlustre/obdfilter/filter_io_26.c:                       \"report this to <http://bugzilla.lustre.org/> , along \"\nlustre/osc/osc_request.c:                               \"but please notify on http://bugzilla.lustre.org/\\n\",\n\nWe obviously shouldn't change the copyright URL, but what about the MODULE_AUTHOR() URL?  We don't want users of our modified code to be bugging Oracle.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
